title: For Sale/Trade:  Tactical Saiga 7.62 x 39 converted AK-47 BANNED
postcontent:
Here's a converted Saiga in 7.62 x 39. These are banned from import thanks to our old friend Obama, so there are no more coming into the U.S. and they are going up and up in price. This bad boy has had the trigger group moved up into the correct position and the trigger guard re-riveted on. It has had a bullet guide welded in and the mag release modified to take 30 round AK mags. It had a Century "Yugo style" pistol grip added and then a Fab Defense adjustable stock put on with adjustable cheek riser. This stock is really nice! It has a Guntec USA quad rail up front and the horrible front sight block was removed and relaced with a surplus Bulgarian sight block and muzzle brake. It's got a railed dust cover to mount a scope, and it's see through, so you can still use the iron sights. Speaking of, the rear leaf was replaced with a Russian 1000m instead of the factory 300m. The safety selector was modified to hold the bolt carrier for a bolt hold open feature that many refer over the factory Saiga bolt hold open. It's got an adjustable bipod and a Tapco 30 round magazine. It's also got a Tapco G2 trigger to eliminate that AK "trigger slap." The entire rifle was refinished with a bake on epoxy coating which looks great and is extremely durable! The rilfe is used and I am not the original owner so I don't know the exact round count, but you can tell by the internals that it is VERY low. The barrel is hammer forged and chrome lined and looks perfect! If you're looking for a top of the line AK, don't wait! Like I said, these are no longer being imported, so the prices are only going in one direction.

I'm in Twin and am asking $1200 for this baby. I will consider trades/partial trades and I'm not opposed to a road trip out Boise way to the West or Idaho Falls way to the East for a serious buyer, but she is first come, first served. Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  Bravo BCM SOCOM upper with Daniel Defense RIS II FSP rail
location: Raleigh / Fayetteville / FT Bragg, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
The SOCOM M4 profile is a mid-weight profile barrel for the M4A1 Carbine. The flats milled under the handguards are for mounting of the M203. SOCOM requested the mid profile to better handle the volume of fire from their shooters. This profile is being adopted as a new standard for the M4A1 Carbine.

The Daniel Defense Rail Interface System (RIS II) was designed at the request of the United States Special Operations Command (SOCOM) for the SOPMOD II program. SOCOM had a specific requirement for a free float M203 solution and Daniel Defense responded, designing a revolutionary product to meet the government’s need. The Daniel Defense RIS II allows the individual operator to free float the M203 grenade launcher without additional parts. As importantly, special tools are not required to mount the M203 grenade launcher. This was accomplished by integrating all of the needed parts to free float the M203 into the rail itself. The Daniel Defense RIS II M4A1 FSP feature a cut-out in the top rail to accommodate a standard front sight base on a carbine-length gas system.

Put about 150 rounds through of different ammo brands, no issues. Also includes a a BCM compensator and magpul backup rear sight.
